The paper deals with a likelihood model for high dimensional data and introduces a new method for capturing correlations among the hidden features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), information theory (cs.IT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Among these, machine learning and artificial intelligence are the most likely categories as the paper focuses on developing a new model for learning hidden features.
